<p>While AU has become carbon neutral, the school does not measure up to other schools in America in terms of green power usage.</p>

<h2 id="future-of-sustainability-at-au">Future of sustainability at AU</h2>

<p>Jesse Cross is the University‚Äôs Zero Waste Manager. He oversees the campus recycling process and works to implement community outreach. He‚Äôs witnessed the evolution of campus sustainability as a student and now a staff member.</p>

<p>‚ÄúThere was a really big push around 2018‚Ä¶with the three bins,‚Äù Cross said in an interview. ‚ÄúWe work with a partner facility, Prince George‚Äôs County Composting Facility, for composting. We can‚Äôt send any contaminates,‚Äù Cross said.</p>

<p>That‚Äôs where student volunteers, <a href="https://www.american.edu/about/sustainability/get-involved/ecorep-program.cfm">EcoReps</a>, come in. One job of the volunteers is to check and sort bags for possible contaminants.</p>

<p>Looking past the last few years, AU has plans to become completely zero waste by 2030‚Äîa step that requires ‚Äúall work on all ends,‚Äù Cross said.</p>

<p>Mimi Beckemeier is an Environmental Studies and Computer Science major, and volunteers at the Office of Sustainability as an EcoRep. Her line of work includes sustainable volunteering, working with 4Ocean, and updating her sustainability blog with resources for the public.</p>

<p>‚ÄúAU is doing a good job of improving‚Ä¶ sustainable living, however, there is always room for improvement. There is a plan in the works for this already, but the biggest thing I would say is to get rid of single-use plastics in our dining halls,‚Äù Beckemeier said.</p>

<p>According to <a href="https://www.usnews.com/education/best-colleges/articles/how-many-universities-are-in-the-us-and-why-that-number-is-changing">U.S. News</a>, there are 3,982 colleges in America. By looking at AU‚Äôs commitment to environmental sustainability, they rank higher than the majority of colleges and universities in the U.S.</p>

<p>This commitment to the environment can be seen in a variety of environmental science and sustainability programs as well as clubs, and even in the Office of Sustainability. To that end, many students also share this commitment to greater environmental justice.</p>

<p>‚ÄúAside from individual actions such as eating less meat, thrifting‚Ä¶there is an abundance of programs, resources and people willing to help students turn sustainable,‚Äù Beckemeier said.</p>

<p>Beckemeier acknowledges that while AU has employed many tactics in overcoming carbon emissions, there are areas that could use improvements, such as plastic-free lunches, farmers‚Äô markets and outdoor events.</p>

<p>‚ÄúIt looks like more environmental organizations, environmental legislation, and more environmental education,‚Äù Beckemeier said.</p>

